            <title>[GROOVY-4648] Pasting into groovy console using shift+insert turns overwrite mode on.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4648</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On windows there are two keyboard shortcut keys for pasting:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ctrl+V&lt;br/&gt;
Shift+Insert&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When pasting using the Shift+Insert into the groovy console script area text-overwrite mode is accidentally enabled by the code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This doesn&apos;t happen when using Ctrl+V, I think there may be a bug in the keyboard handling code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a side note I&apos;m left handed and thus often use shift+insert to paste so I leave one hand on the mouse (and i don&apos;t have to stretch my fingers as far).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not had the chance to test with the latest version of the console, if it&apos;s already fixed please close this bug report.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows 7 x64, via &amp;#39;grails console&amp;#39;.</environment>
